radiographic_examinations.findings: No intrahepatic biliary ductal dilatation. Common duct mildly dilated up to 7 mm, no stones visualized. Gallbladder full with mildly thickened wall and numerous shadowing stones. No intramural edema or pericholecystic fluid. Unremarkable pancreatic head and neck. Possible hypoechoic lesion, possibly artifactual. Hyperechoic liver parenchyma, possibly due to fatty infiltration. Trace free fluid beneath the left lateral liver.
